          <h2 style="font-size:24px;line-height:1.2;font-weight:500;">
        Fight against poverty </h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
         <p style="font-size:18px;line-height:1.5;">
         <strong>
      Summary: 50 world leaders gathered in Seville to discuss global aid amid Trumpâ€™s funding cuts. </strong>
         </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
      The UN's Fourth International Conference on Financing for Development was held in Seville, Spain. It brought together over 50 world leaders and 4,000 representatives. The summit aims to reform international monetary institutions, including the IMF and the World Bank, and establish a <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-1-jul-25-spotlight-h1-4-stable-source-of-funding" target="_blank">stable source of funding</a> for health and education. 
          </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
          Trumpâ€™s reduced <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-1-jul-25-spotlight-h1-5-support-through-usaid" target="_blank">support through USAID</a>, as well as the prioritization of defense spending by Germany, Britain, and France, may compromise the <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-1-jul-25-spotlight-h1-6-un-s-2030-goals" target="_blank">UNâ€™s 2030 goals</a> and increase global poverty. Experts remark that these are the deepest cuts since 1960, highlighting a $4T annual development gap. Trumpâ€™s tariffs and ongoing conflicts in Ukraine and the Middle East further diminish global trade and increase liability burdens. 
       </p>
        <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
       Previous talks in New York produced a <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-1-jul-25-spotlight-h1-7-common-declaration" target="_blank">common declaration</a> to be adopted in Seville. The declaration demanded that development banks triple their lending capacity, urged lenders to ensure predictable funding for essential social spending, and called for more cooperation against tax evasion. However, campaigners have criticized the text for lacking ambition. </p>
        </mj-text>
