          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;padding-top:4px;padding-bottom:6px;">
           <strong>ðŸ‡¨ðŸ‡¦ Canada - Drops controversial tax.</strong> 
           Canada has withdrawn its planned digital services tax on US tech companies just before it was set to take effect, aiming to revive stalled trade talks. The tax, expected to raise $2B from firms like Amazon and Google, had prompted President Trump to disengage negotiations last week, calling the move a blatant attack (<a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-1-jul-25-worldwide-10-talks-back-on" target="_blank">talks back on</a>).
          </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;padding-bottom:6px;">
           <strong>ðŸ‡ºðŸ‡¦ Ukraine - Signs treaty.</strong> 
          President Zelenskyy signed a decree to initiate Ukraineâ€™s withdrawal from the Ottawa Treaty, which bans the use of landmines. Ukraineâ€™s parliament must ratify the withdrawal and formally communicate to the United Nations. He also urged stronger international sanctions against Russia, criticizing the EU's delays (<a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-1-jul-25-worldwide-11-about-the-withdrawal" target="_blank">about the withdrawal</a>).
          </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;padding-bottom:6px;">
           <strong>ðŸ‡®ðŸ‡³ India - Border disputes.</strong> 
